-- UniCredit to receive 3 binding offers for Pioneer unit stake Wed-sources
-- 
-- Wed Jul 30, 2014 05:13AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, July 30 (Reuters) - Three binding offers to buy a stake in Pioneer Investments, the asset management unit of Italian bank UniCredit <CRDI.MI>, are expected on Wednesday, two sources close to the situation said.

"The offers are for a 50 percent stake," one of the sources said, confirming a press report.  The two sources said the whole of Pioneer was worth around 2 billion euros ($2.7 billion).